Before any device testing, read `.agents/skills/soli-testing/SKILL.md` — the on-device testing cookbook (build commands, demo deep links, fixtures, a11y handles, troubleshooting).

Quick reference:
- Android phone: `yarn release --logs` builds, installs, launches, and streams [SoliDev] logs.
- iOS simulator: `yarn ios --logs` (same flow, Release build).
- Automated end-to-end game: `DEMO_GAME_LIMIT=1 yarn release --auto-solve` (or `yarn ios --auto-solve`) — builds, auto-plays the demo playlist, exits on completion.
- When analyzing an issue, add logs first with `devLog` from `src/utils/devLogger.ts` (only emitted with developer mode on; demo deep links enable it).
